<p><strong>Dragon King's Cragblade</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Heavy Thrusting Swords" href="/Heavy+Thrusting+Swords" target="">Heavy Thrusting Sword</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Dragon King's Cragblade</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>, with reduced scaling on <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a>,&nbsp;and is a potent&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;to oppose dragon-like creatures or enemies that are susceptible to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lightning Damage" href="/Lightning+Damage">Lightning</a> damage.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Piercing Gravel Stone sword containing primeval lightning.</em><br><em>A portion of the Dragonlord's power, gained from a</em><br><em>remembrance.</em></p> 
 <p><em>This weapon commands great power over the paltry, mortal</em><br><em>dragons of today.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Dragon King's Cragblade in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Dragon King's Cragblade weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li> <p>Trade <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Remembrance of the Dragonlord" href="/Remembrance+of+the+Dragonlord" target="">Remembrance of the Dragonlord</a>&nbsp;with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia" target="">Enia</a> at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>.</p> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Dragon King's Cragblade Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Thundercloud Form" href="/Thundercloud+Form" target="">Thundercloud Form</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;nor boosted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Dragon King's Cragblade</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Deals +30% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#dragon"><img title="Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>Deals +15% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#ancient-dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#ancient-dragon"><img title="Ancient Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/ancient-dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="ancient dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Ancient Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>This&nbsp;weapon has a special R2 shared with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bloody Helice" href="/Bloody+Helice">Bloody Helice</a>, this also affects its feint animation.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Dragon King's Cragblade</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Dragon King's Cragblade Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Dragon King's Cragblade Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade cannot be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
