				<li id="16680163" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1652404435000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579816/Dragon-King's-Cragblade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">12 May 2022 21:13</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16680163" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">My favourite pvp weapon hands down. The weapon art is something to be used sparingly, its moveset is good enough to where you don&apos;t often even need it, I use it with an offhanded rapier and its super fun. The running r2 is obviously super strong, and it can often put you to the side or even behind an opponent leaving them vulnerable, and if they&apos;re behind they can often try to attack and straight up miss. My only gripe is the actual r1s aren&apos;t amazing, but they can throw off enemies, especially that swipe on the 4th attack. I generally use it to throw off opponents by mixing them with rapier L1s. The actual weapon art is tricky to use consistently but it&apos;s rewarding as all hell to land. Its sheer damage means that as long as you land it and don&apos;t die you have basically won the trade. It seems like an average of 1100 damage, so as long as you&apos;ve hit them at any point during the duel it should leave them practically 1 tap range. Speaking of which the actual hitbox on the cloud can be used to pick, no boring fan dagger pick necessary, just turn into a cloud and anyone not experienced with this weapon won&apos;t expect it to take out the last of their health. Another thing to note is you should absolutely recognise when the art is and isn&apos;t going to hit, as you can aim it away to retreat in cloud form. This allows you to get some stamina back to dodge your opponent punishing.<br/>Overall my favourite weapon to duel with, not the best but the most fun.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16680163" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16680163" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>7</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16680163"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16680163" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16680163"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
