				<li id="16579558" class="cmnt-root" data="-8" data-d="1648614642000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579816/Dragon-King's-Cragblade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">30 Mar 2022 00:30</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16579558" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Dont let that 37 dex requirement fool you. YES YOU CAN use this below level 50 if you know what talismans/helmet to equip (hint you will be very ugly looking) and what armor set to grab. <br/>At +4 its okay at best in pve. You will get your teeth kicked in by a number of bosses if you try to spam the wa. You can hold down the skill button to extend the effect and kind of control it. <br/><br/>In low level pvp this thing is insane. Most folks dont have health leveled for whatever reason so they die in a few its or a single thundercloud form.   However its very far away from being meta. Anyone with half a brain can just circle strafe your wa if you try to spam it, and you will still get obliterated by rivers of blood, magic gank spam and moonveil on occasion. Its alot of fun, it oneshots folks but its not easy to use in pve or pvp and requires a particular investment of resources (also killing a really annoying boss, half a dozen bosses if you count the talismans) not meta. But fun.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16579558" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></spa